# TypeScript Conventions

- Use interfaces for object shapes rather than type aliases
- Follow camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for classes, interfaces, and types
- Prefer async/await over Promise chains
- Use strong typing, avoid any when possible
- Prefer readonly properties when values shouldn't change
- Use function overloads for complex function signatures
- Prefer optional parameters over undefined
- Export named functions instead of default exports